<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-126BB579-BBBE-4506-A102-9C25AD2469B1" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-126BB579-BBBE-4506-A102-9C25AD2469B1" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> How to enter the Sales/Service Organization ID (SOID) on the printer</b> </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M127646-B53"><p class="- topic/p ">The SOID can be entered during the installation in the installation wizard or via the printer operator panel after the installation. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-F2052701-4D44-4295-9BE9-70BF10432301" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Find the SOID to use</title><p class="- topic/p ">In most cases you will know the SOID of your own sales/service organization. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If you do not know it see : 
<xref keyref="FAQDOIS001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-611135E7-18E3-4468-8484-4FA6FE396EBE.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text What to do when you do not know the SOID?>What to do when you do not know the SOID</xref> 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_A0710B5B61E24C17A59F86C851385DD0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Enter the SOID in installation wizard (preferred)</title><p class="- topic/p ">Take a look at the installation wizard section for a complete explanation. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="GININSTWIZZARD001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-36980814-B41B-4AFD-B05F-6D57C557C949.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Installation wizard (Part 1) (todo)?>Installation wizard (part 1) (upto R4.3)</xref> 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_8B673BFBAEAA46C58997BC1DDC390901" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Enter the SOID via the Printer operator panel</title><note id="GUID-46DDB368-7F4D-4E8D-9051-24DA484D8825" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">You need the system administrator password or this procedure. 
</p></note><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap the system button on the printer operator panel 
</p><fig id="GUID-FFC34B6D-60BC-469B-ABA6-C50B5F3CA1F9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0D3EC755-A966-4450-A165-31F7EBC59662-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0D3EC755-A966-4450-A165-31F7EBC59662-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap the remote services button in the screen. 
</p><fig id="GUID-DA8A3197-01A7-48E8-83C0-8F6FADCD6318" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5180A632-9382-4234-A84B-17A7B9B3236D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5180A632-9382-4234-A84B-17A7B9B3236D-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Log in as system administrator. 
</p><fig id="GUID-28EA8152-EB65-4729-80B2-35D9A4672FDE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-168B2B15-6BC4-4D6E-823E-A6C6FC4561D9-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-168B2B15-6BC4-4D6E-823E-A6C6FC4561D9-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You will see the login button change if you entered the correct password. 
</p><fig id="GUID-9FD5614B-5619-4E7E-97BE-8C833E88C569" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E7D1AB6D-E9EB-4B3B-A75E-AC0E2748401F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E7D1AB6D-E9EB-4B3B-A75E-AC0E2748401F-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><fig id="GUID-2069DE1A-61C3-4D29-9161-71756B340676" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3113F6B9-41DB-4723-B806-8EDA78199DD4-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3113F6B9-41DB-4723-B806-8EDA78199DD4-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap remote connection. 
</p><fig id="GUID-F83D9ACF-0DA5-454A-828F-B10AC4E50324" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6DD88F09-F0C3-491B-85C8-FDF1CAA44C02-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6DD88F09-F0C3-491B-85C8-FDF1CAA44C02-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap the fill-in field next to Service Organization ID and enter the SOID. 
</p><note id="GUID-A77B5CC1-67A9-4474-B15C-D10631F9378F" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The SOID number must be entered without hyphen (for instance, if the SOID is 0001-0001, type in 00010001) 
</p></note><fig id="GUID-4EB331A6-D8BA-43E0-82A0-FD443F2B57B7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-58ADBB30-297C-4BDF-B624-0EAFF1089115-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-58ADBB30-297C-4BDF-B624-0EAFF1089115-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Save to save the changes. 
</p></li></ol></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-7D3F358C-1AB9-4A5D-9B0E-C75D689F152E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>